secondary_outcome.description:
This is an exploratory efficacy measure. The average change in points from baseline for participants in the study.
Points 1-7 are defined below:
not hospitalized with resumption of normal activities;
not hospitalized, but unable to resume normal activities;
hospitalized, not requiring supplemental oxygen;
hospitalized, requiring supplemental oxygen;
hospitalized, requiring nasal high-flow oxygen therapy, noninvasive mechanical ventilation, or both;
hospitalized, requiring ECMO, invasive mechanical ventilation, or both;
death.

This is an exploratory efficacy measure. Measured by the number of participants that progress from levels 6-7.
Points 1-7 are defined below:
not hospitalized with resumption of normal activities;
not hospitalized, but unable to resume normal activities;
hospitalized, not requiring supplemental oxygen;
hospitalized, requiring supplemental oxygen;
hospitalized, requiring nasal high-flow oxygen therapy, noninvasive mechanical ventilation, or both;
hospitalized, requiring ECMO, invasive mechanical ventilation, or both;
death.

This is an exploratory efficacy measure. Measured by the number of days by which a change in participant ordinal score is noted.
Points 1-7 are defined below:
not hospitalized with resumption of normal activities;
not hospitalized, but unable to resume normal activities;
hospitalized, not requiring supplemental oxygen;
hospitalized, requiring supplemental oxygen;
hospitalized, requiring nasal high-flow oxygen therapy, noninvasive mechanical ventilation, or both;
hospitalized, requiring ECMO, invasive mechanical ventilation, or both;
death.
